e event patterns:\n   - Line 47-54: Only handles VFileContentChangeEvent with isFromRefresh=false\n   - JetBrains may fire different event types for programmatic edits (PSIChange events, etc.)\n   - Should also listen to DocumentListener or BulkAwareDocumentListener for all document changes\n\n### Suggested Minimal Test/Verification Changes\n\n1. Add debug logging in StackTraceAnalyzer.analyze() to log:\n   - Full call stack when analysis.confidence < HIGH\n   - Stack frames that DON'T match known patterns\n   \n2. In DocumentChangeListener.kt line 113-116, temporarily log even when confidence != HIGH:\n   - See which Copilot/AI edits are being dropped\n   \n3. Create unit test that simulates GitHub Copilot suggesting code edits in JetBrains:\n   - Mock StackTraceAnalyzer responses\n   - Verify checkpoint is triggered with correct agent name/model\n\n---\n\n## Issue 2: Concurrent Repository Commits Fail with daemon.lock Error\n\n### Root Cause\nRace condition in daemon startup synchronization between multiple processes.\n\n**Location:** git-ai/src/commands/daemon.rs, lines 108-124\n\n```rust\n// ensure_daemon_running_attached():\nif daemon_is_up(&config) {           // Check 1: Is daemon running?\n    return Ok(config);\n}\nif daemon_startup_is_blocked(&config) {  // Check 2: Is lock held?\n    return Err(format!(\"daemon startup blocked: lock held at {}\",\n                       config.lock_path.display()));  // <-- ERROR\n}\nspawn_daemon_run_detached(&config)?;     // Try to spawn\n```\n\n**Race Condition:**\n1. Process A: daemon_is_up() → false (no daemon yet)\n2. Process B: daemon_is_up() → false (no daemon yet)\n3. Process A: daemon_startup_is_blocked() tries to acquire lock → succeeds (lock free), **drops lock immediately**\n4. Process B: daemon_startup_is_blocked() tries to acquire lock → succeeds (lock free), **drops lock immediately**\n5. Process A: spawn_daemon_run_detached() acquires lock successfully\n6. Process B: spawn_daemon_run_detached() fails because lock is now held\n   → Returns error: \"daemon startup blocked: lock held at daemon.lock\"\n\n### Root Cause Mechanism\n`daemon_startup_is_blocked()` (lines 216-225) temporarily acquires the lock just to check if it's available, then releases it:\n```rust\nfn daemon_startup_is_blocked(config: &DaemonConfig) -> bool {\n    match LockFile::try_acquire(&config.lock_path) {\n        Some(lock) => {\n            drop(lock);  // <-- IMMEDIATELY RELEASES LOCK\n            false\n        }\n        None => true,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis creates a window where two processes both see the lock as free, but only one can actually acquire it during spawn.\n\n### Suggested Minimal Code Change\n\n**git-ai/src/commands/daemon.rs** - Replace `ensure_daemon_running_attached()` logic:\n\nInstead of:\n```rust\nif daemon_is_up(&config) { return Ok(config); }\nif daemon_startup_is_blocked(&config) { return Err(...); }\nspawn_daemon_run_detached(&config)?;\n```\n\nChange to:\n```rust\nif daemon_is_up(&config) { return Ok(config); }\n\n// Acquire lock early to prevent concurrent spawn attempts\nmatch DaemonLock::acquire(&config.lock_path) {\n    Ok(_lock) => {\n        // We hold the lock now - check again if daemon appeared while we waited\n        if daemon_is_up(&config) {\n            return Ok(config);  // Another process won the race, reuse its daemon\n        }\n        // Safe to spawn with lock held - no other process can also spawn\n        spawn_daemon_run_with_held_lock(&config, _lock)?;\n        // ... wait for daemon up with lock still held or released after spawn...\n    }\n    Err(_) => {\n        // Another process holds the lock and is spawning the daemon\n        // Retry waiting for daemon to come up (with timeout/backoff)\n        if wait_for_daemon_up_with_retries(&config, timeout) {\n            return Ok(config);\n        }\n        return Err(\"daemon failed to start (lock held by other process)\".to_string());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Test Changes\n\nAdd test in git