use lock is now held\n   → Returns error: \"daemon startup blocked: lock held at daemon.lock\"\n\n### Root Cause Mechanism\n`daemon_startup_is_blocked()` (lines 216-225) temporarily acquires the lock just to check if it's available, then releases it:\n```rust\nfn daemon_startup_is_blocked(config: &DaemonConfig) -> bool {\n    match LockFile::try_acquire(&config.lock_path) {\n        Some(lock) => {\n            drop(lock);  // <-- IMMEDIATELY RELEASES LOCK\n            false\n        }\n        None => true,\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis creates a window where two processes both see the lock as free, but only one can actually acquire it during spawn.\n\n### Suggested Minimal Code Change\n\n**git-ai/src/commands/daemon.rs** - Replace `ensure_daemon_running_attached()` logic:\n\nInstead of:\n```rust\nif daemon_is_up(&config) { return Ok(config); }\nif daemon_startup_is_blocked(&config) { return Err(...); }\nspawn_daemon_run_detached(&config)?;\n```\n\nChange to:\n```rust\nif daemon_is_up(&config) { return Ok(config); }\n\n// Acquire lock early to prevent concurrent spawn attempts\nmatch DaemonLock::acquire(&config.lock_path) {\n    Ok(_lock) => {\n        // We hold the lock now - check again if daemon appeared while we waited\n        if daemon_is_up(&config) {\n            return Ok(config);  // Another process won the race, reuse its daemon\n        }\n        // Safe to spawn with lock held - no other process can also spawn\n        spawn_daemon_run_with_held_lock(&config, _lock)?;\n        // ... wait for daemon up with lock still held or released after spawn...\n    }\n    Err(_) => {\n        // Another process holds the lock and is spawning the daemon\n        // Retry waiting for daemon to come up (with timeout/backoff)\n        if wait_for_daemon_up_with_retries(&config, timeout) {\n            return Ok(config);\n        }\n        return Err(\"daemon failed to start (lock held by other process)\".to_string());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Test Changes\n\nAdd test in git-ai/src/tests/ to simulate concurrent daemon startup:\n```rust\n#[test]\nfn test_concurrent_daemon_startup_no_race() {\n    // Spawn 10 threads, each calling ensure_daemon_running\n    // Verify only one daemon starts (one lock acquired, others wait/reuse)\n    // Verify no \"lock held at...\" errors\n}\n```\n\n### Why This Matters\n- **Current behavior:** When 2+ repos commit simultaneously → one succeeds, others get \"daemon startup blocked\" error\n- **Fixed behavior:** All processes safely wait or reuse daemon without errors\n- **No daemon leak:** Lock release semantics still sound (when spawn completes or process exits)\n",
